fix: rewrite MobileNav to match desktop sidebar exactly

Before: 5 mismatched items with wrong labels (Overview, Ledger, Import,
Insights, Profile), wrong icons, a broken /upload route that does not
exist, and entire pages unreachable on mobile (Net Worth, Budgets,
Goals, Loans, Security).

After: a proper bottom tab bar that mirrors the desktop sidebar:

Primary 5 tabs (always visible):
  Dashboard    -- LayoutDashboard icon
  Transactions -- ArrowLeftRight icon
  Budgets      -- PieChart icon
  Goals        -- Target icon
  Loans        -- CreditCard icon

More drawer (tap the ... button to reveal):
  Net Worth | Reports
  Security  | Settings

Active state: var(--primary) text color + var(--primary-light)
background pill, identical to the desktop sidebar-link.active style.

If the current page is one of the More items, the More button itself
lights up in primary color so the user always knows where they are.
